<small>on december 31st i ran into aaron havner. my heart sunk when i saw him and he had the nerve to talk to me. we were alone outside and he bared his life's story to me. he dealt drugs, did drugs, went to jail for a DUI, got arrested four times lost his family, lost his friends. i no longer feel angry about him anymore, now i just pity his life. he said he joined the marines. and then he apologized to me for how he treated me when we were together. he felt horrible and i could tell that he was sincere. so if i ever run into him again, i'll no longer feel the pain. after four odd years, i'm finally over him.
mp3/cd/record/radio/cassette player. pea coat. flannel shirts. nightmare before christmas dvd. the dark knight dvd. season one of pushing daisies. season three of robot chicken. take me here.

<small>i got a new phone! its a sidekick lx and i'm going to give aidee and old sidekick 3 so we can email each other pictures at work. i'm so excited and i can't wait until we hang out again. i've been working a lot more lately. and i just learned silver bullet last week and i really like the cowboy uniform they make us wear. i don't really like the hat but the red suspenders are pretty cool. i'm such a dork . . .

but anyway life has been pretty good. i've been wanting to move out and i hope i will be able to soon cause my parents and sisters have been such jerks lately and i just want to get away from them. i'm really tired of them and they yell at me for no good reason and i don't want their shit anymore. i really don't.

i've been missing a lot of people. i used to be such good friends with so many people and i've lost all complete touch with them. and i hate it so much. but yeah . . . i'm at work right now. well "on lunch" so i gotta head back. k. bye.

so halloween haunt has been taking up all of my time. at least theres only two nights left. not much has really happened. i got my new tattoo. or should i say tattooS. im so excited. but it left me flat broke. 

i stay up too late at night. and wake up too late. i go to bed like at five and wake up at two. i don't know how i'm going to go back to the regular schedule. baaaahhh.

i need a new phone so bad. my sidekick has been pissing me off lately. i've dropped it too many times and the menu button came off. it sucks.

i love mondays. cause i get to hang out with aidee all day. she's the only one i still really talk to from high school. and she's helping me quit smoking. i didn't want to do it alone so we're doing it together. 

ok, i'm done for now.

what a fantastic cinco de mayo. haha.

now i'm just sitting in my room watching across the universe for the millionth time. but i love it. and jim sturgess. <3

<small>ok, so i went to the ATS show tonight and it was a lot of fun.i got to meet a lot of cool people. and after the show we all decided to go to the westminster cafe to eat. so we get there and we're all hanging out in the parking lot waiting for everybody and my heart just stops.
i saw aaron havner. my enitire body cringe and i just wanted to die. it was so FUCKING horrible. i don't think he saw me cause i ducked down the second i saw him. i thought i was over all of that shit. but i guess no one can really recover from what he did to me. i can't get him out of my head now. and i hate it. cause i spent months just thinking about him. and i thought i was over it all. but just seeing him triggered all of the memories back. 
i want to forget. i want to forget so FUCKING bad.

<small>i'm in yucca valley right now. mel, fish and i got here a couple of days ago. before we got here we went to idyllwild. we took a tram up to the mountains and played in the snow. it was such an amazing experience cause i've never seen snow.
then we got to yucca valley and i met mel's dad. he's so cool.

the next day, mel, fish and i went to the living desert which is a zoo in palm desert. it was soo awesome. i got to see a bunch of cool animals.

there's this place behind mel's dad's house with giant statues of jesus. its soo freaky. and eerie. i didn't like that so much. 

and today was our lazy day where we only went thrift store shopping in stores around the neighborhood.

we're going to be heading back tomorrow morning. it's been really nice doing this. it's like a vacation. no work for four days. its really really nice.

but anyway, i'll make sure to post ALL of the pictures up when i get home.

i miss brandon. and my friends. and this might sound really weird, but i miss some of my co workers. i mean i'm used to seeing them like everyday and it's weird not talking to them and stuff.

<small>i was at riptide and i was walking on the platform and there was a shoe sole on the floor so i picked it up and asked everyone if they lost their "soul". it was so funny to me. but no one else laughed. i felt pretty lame, but didn't really care.

so matt went back to wyoming after only being back here for like five days. i worked all of those days. but he wanted to see me so he came over to my house like at midnight on thursday even though he had to leave at six in the morning on friday. it was good seeing him. he'll be back in three months.

i haven't been able to sleep AT ALL lately. it sucks. i like sleeping.

no boy troubles. no boys at all. i hate it. i don't know why, but sometimes i feel like a desperately need a guy. to be there for me, and so i could be there for him. i don't like this. it's dumb.

the new year is almost here. i don't like it. i don't like even numbers. can we just skip to 2009? i'm going to be 20 in 2009. how weird it that? super weird.

ok. i think that's pretty much it. until next time. k.thanks.bye.

i'm staring at my feet my cheeks are turning red i'm searching for the words inside my head i'm feeling nervous trying to be so perfect cause i know you're worth it if i could say what i want to say i'd say i want to blow you away be with you every night am i squeezing you too tight? i guess i'm wishing my life away with these things i'll never say." i saw him today for like five minutes. he hugged me twice. it was sweet. i love it when guys hug me around the waist. i feel so comfortable and safe. i love his hugs. cause its not awkward or anything. he embraces me and makes it seem like theres no one else but us. winsor is moving to chicago. he's really going to do it. and i'm going to miss him. i'll never forget all the times we've hung out in his car. when it was just the two of us and he'd be himself. i'll always remember our first kiss. and our last one. i hope he'll be happy there. i'm almost done christmas shopping. i love wrapping the presents. and i bought some super cute wrapping paper too. i don't know what to get my family. i mean, its weird cause i knew what i was going to get my friends. but i spend more time with my friends then my family.

i don't even know what i want. it's weird, cause there's always one thing that i would really like, but there's nothing right now.
well, having him would be nice. but i know that i can't have him. its tooooo weird. i haven't seen him in a while. well, three days, but i'm so used to seeing him everyday. -_-

aidee got me addicted to guitar hero. lol. i love it sooooo much. we played last night for like four hours straight. i love aidee.

<small>so i guess i haven't really updated my livejournal in a while. been too busy with work and such. exciting things don't really happen anymore. i got a tattoo. that's new. i got it at the same place eddie got his. well, he referred them to me. my family doesn't know. i really don't know how to tell them. "oh by the way i got a tattoo two weeks ago." i don't know.
don't really have any boy trouble cause there aren't any boys. which i really don't like. lately i've been feeling really lonely. even when i'm with around people i still feel lonely and i hate it. sooooooooo much. sosososososososososososososososo much. but there's really nothing i can do about it. i think thats what kills me the most. 
but anyway, i want to quit knotts. i need to find another job first though. everyone is leaving. jason, bree and michael got fired. brett quit. david and jackie are going to quit. theres only to reasons why i'm here right now. i need the money and i'm going to miss my co workers. i've made a lot of friends here. and i like them because they don't know anything about my past. thats the good thing. they don't know the horrible things i've done. and i've done some pretty horrible shit. 

they're making a movie out of chuck palanhuik's book "choke" it's my favorite book of his. i can't wait until it comes out next year. it better be good. i don't want to be dissappointed. but most books that are made into movies aren't that great. they always leave oout the little details that i like or change something completely. fight club was a really good book and movie. i love edward norton though.
there was a guy that rode boomerang earlier and i thought he looked exactly like edward norton. i wanted to take a picture with him and tell people that i met edward norton. i'm such a dork.

well, time to get back to work.
fuck.

k. bye.

And at the same time I was talking to loren ans he showed me a song he wrote. It was a song about me. It was so so so cute. Its called "story of your life" www.myspace.com/twotonechat. <small>So I'm on my lunch right now. Things with adam are really good. We've actually been joking around and stuff. Hahaha. I thought that that would never happen in a million years. Well, I don't know when we are going to talk to amy, but I have a feeling that its going to go well. Or at least I hope so. I still want to be cross trained over at perilous. But I guess we'll see. 

Today is so fucken hot. And its a really slow day. I think that I am about to fall asleep.

And on another note, I've decided to just stay single. I'm not going to pursue anyone anymore. Ill let the guy some to me. If it was meant to be, it will.
Why do I always go for the guy I can't have? I'm dumb. Don't listen to me. Hahaha.

So here I am. At lakeside, listening to interpol, with a cigerette, mountain dew and my sidekick. I am pretty content. And I've decided not to talk to jacob anymore for betraying me. It was harsh. I'm still a little frustrated, but ill live on.

I'm alive and thankful for what I have. We all should be. A lot of people have it worse. And I hope that they will be able to live on too. 

The world works in mysterious ways. And I am not going to let it get me down. I am going to go through my life, whether it be another 50 years or days or hours. I will live and try to live it happily.

I guess we all have to get through life one day at a time. And today, I feel good. I feel strong. I feel independent. I feel confident. I feel like myself again.

And it feels amazing. 




Time to go back to work. And I don't mind it at all.

<small> so I have pretty much realized that I can't trust anyone from work. Some of them gossip way too much and I hate it. There was someone that I actually trusted and he betrayed me. Now, I think I'm just going to keep everything to myself or tell my real friends and not the people that I work with. Its insane! Lies spread through out knott's like a wildfire. I don't know what I'm going to do. It's going to take a pretty long time before I trust anyone from work again. And I hate that I'm saying this because I really like some of them. I should've known better. I guess it was a lapse in judgement on my behalf. But now I know. My trust will be the hardest thing to gain. 

So things with adam have gotten somewhat better. We talked on the phone last night at like midnight for about a half an hour. Talking about what we're going to say to amy and how we are going to try to work things out. I really thought that we would end up hanging up on each other, but we really had a nice civilized conversation. So I guess I'm going to try to work with him and see how it goes. I don't know what everyone else is going to say because they hate him. But he brought up a lot of good points. So yeah.

So I'm using my sidekick right now. I'm so excited. I love it. I'm never going to put it down. Haha.


Work in a little bit. Lets see how it goes. Ill probably update during my lunch or something. K. Bye.

sunday: 11:30 - 10:15 yesterday i had a nervous breakdown at work because people were yelling and cursing at me. then i got knee-ed, elbowed, and spat at. i couldn't help but break down and cry right there. it was awful. i wanted to get away. but i couldn't. but my co-workers were really nice. nathan and his mom gave me a ride home after work. his mom is soooo nice. i really like her. i hope i get to see her again sometime soon. nathan acts the same he does in front of friends and his mom. it was weird. we went to rallys and they told me stories of when nathan was younger. i'm really falling for him. today, i got yelled at again. i had to hold seats for a handicapped person and the lady i asked to wait another turn yelled at me. and then later on, an old "handicapped" man started yelling at me because i let another handicapped person on before him. i only did that because his appointment was before his. the other handicapped person only had one leg. they started arguing and then i started crying again. then hyperventilating. but i had to keep on working. it was so hard. the old man and his group left. the guy with one leg gave me a hug and apologized for arguing and stuff. a random lady hugged me and said i was doing a great job. another lady said that its ok and if i wanted, they were going to get drinks later and wanted me to join them. and that was it. i went on my break and josh talked to me and helped me out. i went back to work and that was it. i'm starting to think that i'm not cut out for this job.

<small>i've been making most of my entries just for friends. so yeah.

yesterday i woke up at six o'clock in the morning and drove to san luis obispo with my mom, sister, brandon, and mike. we had to go pick up my sister's car from the impound lot. but yeah, it took about four hours to get there, spent an hour there, and then five more hours back do to traffic. got home around six, missed a call from matt so i called him.

he came over to pick me up [w/ jorge and daniel] and we went to newport beach to see a show. atrementous [or whatever] was good. axiomatic workshop was pretty good too. i don't really remember the third band because they sucked and we spent the entire time out in the patio area. the last person to play was this girl named ruby. i loved her. she had an amazing voice and i loved the lyrics.

overall, pretty good day. i got to have some talk time with mike and i've been too busy working to spend time with him. matt and i finally hung out. maybe again sometime soon. and now i gotta get ready for work today.
